            Torres examines Holloway with obvious skepticism and says, "You're… a plant."

            Holloway replies, "I'm a sentient being who values individual voices contributing to collective harmony. Kira's voice matters here."

            Torres says, "This is highly irregular."

            I say, "Belonging usually is."

            Torres turns back to me and says, "Ms. Voss, I need to be absolutely certain this is your genuine choice and not coercion or impairment. What would convince me?"

            I say, "Let me show you—tour the facility, talk to everyone, see what we've built together—then decide if this looks like captivity or community."

            Torres exchanges looks with Dr. Chen, then nods. Torres says, "Show me."
